sfn_lines = [
    "Enclosures shall comply with IEC 62208 for empty enclosures and shall be suitable for assemblies compliant with IEC 61439‑1&2 for pumping motor control and automation panels",
    "The enclosure shall provide a minimum ingress protection of IP55 according to IEC 60529, maintaining protection after installation of panels/doors and standard accessories",
    "The enclosure shall provide IK10 mechanical protection with solid doors and IK08 with glazed doors according to IEC 62262, suitable for industrial pumping environments.",
    "The enclosure shall have an epoxy‑polyester structured finish providing corrosion resistance at least C2H according to ISO 12944.",
    "The enclosure shall be constructed using decarbonized steel manufactured with recycled materials and renewable energy sources to minimize the product’s carbon footprint, supporting sustainability requirements in water infrastructure projects."
    "The enclosure structure shall withstand a minimum static load of 1500 kg, enabling installation of high‑power pumping equipment and dense component layouts"
    "The solid door shall support at least 60 kg load, with the possibility to increase up to 90 kg using a centering caster accessory, ensuring safe operation with heavy door‑mounted devices (HMI, indicators, documentation)."
    "The enclosure shall use a bolted structure enabling disassembly into top/bottom frames and uprights, providing flexibility for maintenance, transportation, and customization compared to welded structures."
    "The enclosure system shall allow combination of cabinets in all directions and door mounting on any side without special accessories, to adapt pumping station layouts and future extensions"
    "A kit version shall be available allowing back‑to‑back associations without loss of rear panels, creation of frames without doors/panels, and mounting of doors on side parts, enabling complex pumping assemblies."
    "The supplier shall guarantee exact compliance with catalogue dimensions to ensure compatibility with pre‑engineered pumping panel layouts and site civil works interfaces."
    "Doors shall be reversible with 120° opening (and 180° with accessory), and handle options shall accommodate most locks on the market, with a standard 5 mm double‑bar insert."
    "For double‑door enclosures, the second door shall be operated by a dedicated handle, ensuring safe access and operation without reaching inside the cabinet."
    "The cabinet shall include a quick‑fixation system for the mounting plate, providing temporary hold to allow the operator sufficient time to complete final fixation safely and efficiently."
    "The manufacturer shall provide PEP/RoHS and complete 2D/3D/CAD data compatible with SEE Electrical / IGE XAO, EPLAN and WSCAD to support engineering and lifecycle management of water pumping bundles.",
]
